 three areas at the same time and as early as possible.
 Stephen Cook elected to work on the Interfacing Hardware Design, while
 James worked on the Interfacing Logic Design and Stuart on the Analogue
 Audio Design; these allocations reflected the areas of expertise that had
 already been established.
 
\layout Standard

The remaining roles of Project Manager and Documentation were given to Stephen
 Cook and Iain Todd respectively; while Iain acknowledged his weaknesses
 with documentation, he felt that this role was more suitable than either
 software or hardware.
 Stephen Cook agreed to split his time between his managerial role and his
 tasks in hardware design.
\layout Subsection

